# mkdb weekly sync schedule. Source of truth — what `crontab -l` on the VPS
# should show. Install (or re-install after a rebuild) with:
#
#     crontab scripts/mkdb.crontab
#
# Verify with `crontab -l`. The VPS timezone is America/New_York, so the
# times below are Eastern (check with `timedatectl`; if it ever drifts off
# America/New_York, run `timedatectl set-timezone America/New_York` first).
#
# Why `\%F` instead of `%F`: cron treats an unescaped `%` as a newline inside
# the command field, which truncates the command. The backslash forces a
# literal `%`, so when cron actually invokes the shell, `$(date +%F)` runs
# at fire time and the log file is dated for the day it actually ran.

PATH=/usr/bin:/bin

# Sun 5:00 PM ET — fire the scheduler wrapper, which sleeps until the
# computed start time (next midnight − max of last 5 syncs' duration − 30 min
# buffer) and then runs the actual sync. 5 PM gives the wrapper up to 7
# hours of headroom — plenty for any realistic max-duration since steady-
# state syncs run ~50 min. See scripts/scheduled-sync.ts.
#
# SYNC_MIN_BUDGET_MS=9000000 (2h 30m) is a temporary override active while
# the first few lank-inclusive syncs build up history. Without it, the
# scheduler would still use the metro-only max from prior weeks (~1h 10m)
# even though the new run pulls ratings for ~14 additional lycan-only users
# and may run longer. Remove the override once the 5-week lookback contains
# enough lank-inclusive runs to reflect the new steady-state.
0 17 * * 0 cd /root/mkdb && SYNC_MIN_BUDGET_MS=9000000 npm run sync:scheduled >> dumps/sync_$(date +\%F).log 2>&1

# Mon 12:00 AM ET — swap staging into live, recompute similarity, append the
# new ranking week, trim history, delete orphan films + posters. Promote
# itself takes ~30 sec. After it succeeds, push both top-1000 lists to
# Letterboxd via the API (metro first, then lank). Each list update takes
# ~7-8 min, so total ~16-17 min finishing by ~00:17 AM Monday. Requires
# LETTERBOXD_REFRESH_TOKEN. && short-circuits on any earlier failure so
# stale data isn't pushed to Letterboxd.
0  0 * * 1 cd /root/mkdb && npm run promote && npm run update-letterboxd-list:metro && npm run update-letterboxd-list:lank >> dumps/promote_$(date +\%F).log 2>&1
